article.headline: Cal Poly-SLO 58, Pacific 39
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Shawn Lewis posted his first double-double of the season with 15 points and 15 rebounds to lead Cal Poly past Pacific 58-39 on Saturday night. David Hanson scored 21 points and contributed eight rebounds for the Mustangs (11-11, 6-4 Big West), who have won three in a row and posted their biggest winning margin of the season. Allen Huddleston scored 13 points for Pacific (13-10, 5-5). It was the second time this season that the Tigers managed only 39 points against Cal Poly -- the Mustangs won the teams' earlier meeting, 43-39 on Jan. 6 in Stockton, Calif. Pacific led 7-0, but Cal Poly came back to lead 13-11 and held a 19-17 lead at halftime. An 11-0 run in the second half extended the Mustangs' lead to 40-24.
